name: glutathione-disulfide reductase
classes: Acting on a sulfur group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
reaction: 2 glutathione + NADP+ = glutathione disulfide + NADPH + H+ [RN:R00115]
comment: A dimeric flavoprotein (FAD); activity is dependent on a redox-active disulfide in each of the active centres.

references.title: Structural studies on crystalline glutathione reductase from human erythrocytes.
